<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,152,332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
This species was previously treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Weinreich" box="[614,819,152,178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" refString="Weinreich, E. (1960) Revision sudamerikanischer Lucanidae (Ins. Col.), II Die Gattungen Charagmophorus, Metadorcus, Scortizus, Apterodorcus, Beneshius, Sclerostomus und Pycnosiphorus (Tafel 3 - 12). Senckenbergiana Biologica, 41 (1 - 2), 41 - 95." type="journal article" year="1960">
Weinreich (
<number box="[750,811,152,178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" value="1960.0">1960</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and the subgenus 
<emphasis box="[1038,1216,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Sclerostominus</emphasis>
erected for it. The characters used by Weinreich were the truncate anterior angles of the pronotum, setose mentum, and the lack of temporal processes in the male. Despite these autapomorphies, the species agrees with 
<taxonomicName box="[1207,1362,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Sclerostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1207,1362,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Sclerostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the characters used here to redefine the genus, thus we consider 
<emphasis box="[914,1103,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Sclerostominus</emphasis>
to be a junior synonym of 
<emphasis box="[151,313,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
<taxonomicName box="[151,309,306,331]" class="Insecta" family="Lucanidae" genus="Sclerostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new synonymy">Sclerostomus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[321,501,306,332]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">new synonymy</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
